ETC-650.description:
Context:
Currently when having props that use accordions do not persist the state of the opened accordions, we should store this in the session storage.
E.g. using this: [https://runed.dev/docs/utilities/persisted-state](<https://runed.dev/docs/utilities/persisted-state>)

Proposed syntax (to make it persist in both the editor and the instance):

```
{
  [componentId]: {
    [propkey]: true/false
  }
}

// So like this
{
  12: {
     "props.group1": false,
     "props.group1.group2": true
  }
}
```

AC:

- [X] Top-level groups default to open on mount when no persisted state exists
- [X] Nested groups default to open (editor) / closed (instance) when no persisted state exists
- [X] Opening/closing a group accordion persists across page reloads (session storage)
- [X] Opening/closing a group accordion persists across builder navigation (selecting different elements)
- [X] Accordion state is scoped per component: two different components with a same-named group have independent states
- [X] Repeater item accordion state is also persisted
- [X] Editor and instance share the same accordion state
